<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-02T13:14:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-02T13:14:00-05:00" n="401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/383.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-02T13:00:00-05:14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The American Consul General at Guayaquil telegraphed this morning that
                            our consular agent at Esmeraldas reports that that city is practically
                            besieged by the revolutionists and that the situation is becoming
                            difficult.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>